        <h1>Download</h1>

        <div class="fullwidth-box">
            <h3 class="full-width-left">How to install the data:</h3>
            <br>
            <h4>General Information</h4>
            X Plane stores the navigational data in two different text-like files called earth_fix.dat and earth_nav.dat found in the "X-Plane/Resource/default data/" directory.<br>
            The earth_fix.dat just contains all FIX points, the earth_nav.dat on the other hand contains all navaids like NDB, VOR, ILS, LOC, glideslope and marker beacons.
            <br>
            <br>
            <h4>Quick Installation Guide</h4>
            Simply open the earth_fix.dat and/or earth_nav.dat file in a text editor of your choice and copy the data from the corresponding box below. Paste the data above the last row "99".<br>Save the file - and you are done. That's it.
            <p>&nbsp;</p>

            <h4>7 Steps for Installation</h4>
            <div>
                <ul>
                    <li>1) open one of the two files into a text editor of your choice</li>
                    <li>2) click into the corresponding box (should light up pink)</li>
                    <li>3) mark the whole list (strg-a)</li>
                    <li>4) copy (strg-c)</li>
                    <li>5) switch to the text editor with the corresponding file</li>
                    <li>6) scroll down and paste the copied list above the last row "99"</li>
                    <li>7) save the file and you are done.</li>
                </ul>
            </div>

        </div>

        <p>&nbsp;</p>
